{"title": "Only Serves for Life", "content": "A President for Life expects to hold office for quite a while. This isn't necessarily the case: although the post cannot technically be vacated with the office holder's deposition, it can quite easily be vacated at any time via his death. This is often mentioned in the context of a threat.\n\nIf a President for Life manages to remain as a ruler even after they died, it becomes The Necrocracy.\n\nSee also Klingon Promotion, In It for Life.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OnlyServesForLife", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/LicenceToKill", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheTamuli", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Discworld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Gor", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/WarriorCats", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ASongOfIceAndFire", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Rihannsu", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/Shadowrun", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheSimpsons"], "non_media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Discworld/MakingMoney", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PresidentForLife", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PresidentForLife", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheNecrocracy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KlingonPromotion", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InItForLife", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Comicbook/XWingSeries", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBad", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BananaRepublic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PresidentForLife", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Discworld/NightWatch", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VetinariJobSecurity", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoxedCrook", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Discworld/GoingPostal", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Discworld/MakingMoney", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PenalColony", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KlingonPromotion", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CatsHaveNineLives", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LeaderWannabe", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Pirate", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GatlingGood", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PresidentForLife", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/Bangladesh", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InvokedTro